		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><add>&#63;</add> MSS. p. 20&#44; note 16 &#40;continued&#41;</p>
				<p>vide everything necessary for our religious worship.  When<lb/> with the advice of his assistants shall from time to time<lb/> propose such regulations as may be necessary for the good<lb/> government of the society.  He shall be obliged to call his<lb/> junta the <date>first Sunday in every month</date> and keep a book of<lb/> their proceedings wrote in a legible hand and good manner&#59;<lb/> which book shall be laid before the members at large when&#45;<lb/>ever he is requested to do it &#40;by a majority&#41;.  No rules or<lb/> regulations shall be considered as binding on the congre&#45;<lb/>gation until it is read 2 <date>shabbath</date> or holidays separately in<lb/> the synagogue&#44; Should any member object to the same it must<lb/> be  by a letter to the parnas within 24 hours after the last<lb/> publication&#44; who shall be obliged to call a meeting of all<lb/> the members in town&#44; when a majority present at such meeting&#44;<lb/> which must be 2<lb/>3 of the members in town&#44; shall <sic>deterim</sic><lb/> the same and the <sic>teremination</sic> shall be binding on the objecting<lb/> member &#40;and all the rest&#41;.  He shall give four copies of the<lb/> laws now made with the proceedings of the juntas shall be de&#45;<lb/>livered to his successor with all books and papers belonging<lb/> to the congregation.  He shall when a yahid has a son born<lb/> give him the distribution of all the mitzvoth on the following<lb/> <date>shabbath</date> and must be called for the sefer.  And when his wife<lb/> comes to shul after lying&#45;in of a son or a daughter&#44; must  be<lb/> called to the sefer.</p>
				<p>4.  The duty of the assistants shall be to assist the parnas in<lb/> the execution of his office.  They shall be obliged to attend<lb/> him on the <date>fourth Sunday of every month</date>&#59; and report to the<lb/> congregation <hi rend="underline">any improper conduct that they may observe by</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">him</hi>&#44; and such complaint to be laid before the Yahidim for</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>MSS. p. 20&#44; note 16 &#40;concluded&#41;</p>
				<p>their determination.</p>
				<p>5.  In the absence of the parnas the senior assistant shall<lb/> officiate and so in rotation the 7 hathan torah and in his<lb/> absence the hathan bereshith.</p>
